  "text": "ACE polymorphism and the risk of COPD of the vasodilator nitric oxide and prostaglandins. [CITATION_1] Olson et al suggested that the vasodilation effect of ACE inhibitor was improved through maximization of the bioavailability of bradykinin. [CITATION_2] As previously mentioned, ACE D polymorphism is associated with a higher concentration and activity of circulating and tissue ACE, which increases the predisposition to COPD with PH.",
